Mediacorp Channel 5's television series Tanglin is a long-form drama series produced by Mediacorp Studios from 2015 to 2017. It centres on the lives of multiracial and multi-generational families â€“ the Tongs, Bhaskars, Rahmans and Lims - living in a middle income neighbourhood of Tanglin; their lives reflect the joys, trials and tribulations of everyday Singaporeans.
The show began airing on Mediacorp Channel 5 on 30 June 2015.
